<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1175,1322]" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1215,1241]" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Ophidiid with head anteriorly depressed; snout long and projecting over mouth; depth at anus about 10 times in standard length; eyes very small; opercle with a strong and curved spine; 3 lateral lines with circular organs.
